Properties shall have unique names for mapping within categories.
PD shall manage the logic view (PD_logic_view), data view (PD_data_view) and style view (PD_style_view).
If an element to be connected in PD_data_view is defined, it shall have a PK like a GUID.
When a property style is defined, the category and attribute name need to be defined so that the property can be identified.
The PD style view shall define how to format the data to enhance understanding and meaning.
The PD data view, similar to a data filter, shall define which BIM element the data set shall be linked with and imported from the external database.
The PD logic view shall define how to import the data set from an external database.
With a property definition to map in PD_data_view, a category to group similar properties can be defined. A category has name.
runtime is capability to identify the types of element. The types are building information components such as walls, doors, and rooms.

geometry is capability to contain the solid information including B-rep (boundary representation) based on Solid. The B-rep information must include the topology such as the vertex, edge, loop and faces.
